        <num>243.520</num>
        <content>
          <p>The department may, on its own initiative or on the complaint of any person, institute administrative proceedings before the board to revoke or suspend any license.A license may be revoked or suspended only after the licensee has been afforded the opportunity for a hearing conducted in accordance with KRS . The department may issue an emergency order pursuant to  to summarily suspend a license upon finding that continued operation of the license holder pending a hearing would constitute a threat to the public health, safety, or welfare.</p>
